00:03:53.940 --> 00:03:55.560
And so I talked to some people.

00:03:55.560 --> 00:03:58.500
And the one thing that seemed
to come up a lot for gamers

00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:02.140
is how do I get my
game to stand out?

00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:06.160
And so that's what I'm going
to kind of look at today.

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:08.677
So so I'm going
to-- let's forget

00:04:08.677 --> 00:04:10.510
the stuff where you
follow style guidelines,

00:04:10.510 --> 00:04:13.340
and all that stuff to
get yourself promoted.

00:04:13.340 --> 00:04:18.209
Maybe within the play game store
or whatever, or the app store.

00:04:18.209 --> 00:04:20.769
We're going to look at stuff
that can influence you.

00:04:20.769 --> 00:04:23.590
So let's take a step
back and-- let's

00:04:23.590 --> 00:04:25.120
say you're developing a game.

00:04:25.120 --> 00:04:28.320
And usually, when I talk to
game developers, you know,

00:04:28.320 --> 00:04:31.150
they may have like
something like video sharing

00:04:31.150 --> 00:04:33.344
on the list of things to do.

00:04:33.344 --> 00:04:34.760
But as you guys
know, when you get

00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:37.302
closer to launching,
or launching,

00:04:37.302 --> 00:04:39.510
whether that's a new game
or a new feature, you know,

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:41.100
you probably
something took longer

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:43.558
than you thought it would, have
and you have to cut things.

00:04:43.558 --> 00:04:46.930
And maybe you have to decide
between a new level and that

00:04:46.930 --> 00:04:49.740
enabling video sharing
or something like that.

00:04:49.740 --> 00:04:52.330
And it usually gets cut.

00:04:52.330 --> 00:04:56.220
And what people tell me is like
well, a minority of our users

00:04:56.220 --> 00:04:56.960
actually use it.

00:04:56.960 --> 00:04:59.725
So we didn't think
it was worthwhile.

00:04:59.725 --> 00:05:01.350
We thought the extra
level or something

00:05:01.350 --> 00:05:03.540
like that would be better.

00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:06.380
And so, actually
looked into that.

00:05:06.380 --> 00:05:08.380
And you'd be right.

00:05:08.380 --> 00:05:12.570
Only 10 to 20% of users,
mobile game users,

00:05:12.570 --> 00:05:15.670
find that feature to
be very important.

00:05:15.670 --> 00:05:19.070
And this was from a study
that Amplifier did last year.

00:05:19.070 --> 00:05:21.550
So this is sharing.

00:05:21.550 --> 00:05:23.175
And what they meant
by this, it doesn't

00:05:23.175 --> 00:05:24.410
mean like sharing
your high score,

00:05:24.410 --> 00:05:25.660
saying, hey, I like this game.

00:05:25.660 --> 00:05:28.900
It means sharing a screen--
three things sharing a screen

00:05:28.900 --> 00:05:32.640
shot, but, more importantly,
sharing video replay,

00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:33.930
or live video.

00:05:33.930 --> 00:05:37.780
So that's-- this 10 to 20%
said it's very important.

00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:39.780
And what this survey
wanted to try to figure out

00:05:39.780 --> 00:05:44.150
was, you know, is it worth going
after these people, or is it

00:05:44.150 --> 00:05:45.560
not?

00:05:45.560 --> 00:05:48.150
So again, this is mobile
gamers only, this study.

00:05:48.150 --> 00:05:50.394
But they dove into
a lot of questions

00:05:50.394 --> 00:05:51.560
and they separated that out.

00:05:51.560 --> 00:05:54.280
So what they did is they
took that group of people

00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:56.409
and they labeled them sharers.

00:05:56.409 --> 00:05:57.950
And then they figured
out how do they

00:05:57.950 --> 00:06:00.690
compare to the non-sharers?

00:06:00.690 --> 00:06:03.391
Now again, both are
mobile game players.

00:06:03.391 --> 00:06:05.140
And what they found
is pretty interesting.

00:06:05.140 --> 00:06:11.010
So first, sharers download
and try more games per month.

00:06:11.010 --> 00:06:15.440
They actually play more per
week, more hours per week.

00:06:15.440 --> 00:06:17.950
They make more purchases,
which is great, right?

00:06:17.950 --> 00:06:20.740
That's in app in the
games themselves.

00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:24.136
And then, lastly,
they're more social.

00:06:24.136 --> 00:06:26.260
So they're going to share
the game play experiences

00:06:26.260 --> 00:06:29.860
with people, not only
online but offline.

00:06:29.860 --> 00:06:33.760
They want to recommend them,
which is also a great thing.

00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:36.260
So you're probably thinking, OK.

00:06:36.260 --> 00:06:39.740
So there's this subset that's
a little bit more important.

00:06:39.740 --> 00:06:40.500
That make sense.

00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:41.830
But I'm still on the fence.

00:06:41.830 --> 00:06:46.900
Like it still doesn't seem
like it's worth the work.

00:06:46.900 --> 00:06:50.890
And this one's pretty
obvious, but mobile gamers

00:06:50.890 --> 00:06:51.740
watch game videos.

00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:54.934
So in the survey, they ask
them a bunch of questions.

00:06:54.934 --> 00:06:56.350
And there's a
couple that came out

00:06:56.350 --> 00:06:58.960
that I thought were
really important.

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.560
And this is one of them.

00:07:00.560 --> 00:07:06.600
So 65% of people, of mobile
gamers, watch video game play.

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:09.040
80% of the sharers
watched it, as well.

00:07:09.040 --> 00:07:10.610
So they were a bit higher.

00:07:10.610 --> 00:07:12.110
But what's really
interesting there,

00:07:12.110 --> 00:07:13.500
is they broke out
the categories.

00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:15.400
They didn't just
say video game play.

00:07:15.400 --> 00:07:19.500
They said live streaming,
trailers, video game play.

00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:22.980
And video replay, or
watching actual game play,

00:07:22.980 --> 00:07:24.230
was rated number one.

00:07:24.230 --> 00:07:26.990
It was actually
rated above trailers.

00:07:26.990 --> 00:07:29.040
So think about
that for a second.

00:07:29.040 --> 00:07:31.950
People-- it's more important
to them to watch the game

00:07:31.950 --> 00:07:35.640
play than these $1,000
or million dollar

00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:37.710
trailers that are put out.

00:07:37.710 --> 00:07:40.497
So keep that in
the back your head.

00:07:40.497 --> 00:07:42.330
And then what really
kind of drove this home

00:07:42.330 --> 00:07:45.450
for me was this other
question that I found was,

00:07:45.450 --> 00:07:48.930
when a mobile gamer
goes and watches

00:07:48.930 --> 00:07:53.950
a game play clip, what's their
number one action afterwards?

00:07:53.950 --> 00:07:56.980
And what they found, was
that 45% of the time they

00:07:56.980 --> 00:07:58.950
download the game.

00:07:58.950 --> 00:07:59.800
That was number one.

00:07:59.800 --> 00:08:03.000
Number two is they would
share it or refer it.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:06.140
And then, number three, was
they continue researching.

00:08:06.140 --> 00:08:09.510
So think about
that for a second.

00:08:09.510 --> 00:08:12.260
These free-- they're
making these for free,

00:08:12.260 --> 00:08:13.751
these game play videos.

00:08:13.751 --> 00:08:15.250
They have a high
click through rate.

00:08:15.250 --> 00:08:18.190
I mean, you're spending
money making these trailers.

00:08:18.190 --> 00:08:21.282
And these free things
are watched more,

00:08:21.282 --> 00:08:22.740
and have a good
click-through rate.

00:08:22.740 --> 00:08:25.000
Like why aren't you
taking advantage of it?

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:26.690
That's what I like to say.

00:08:26.690 --> 00:08:29.850
So hopefully that at least
get you thinking about,

00:08:29.850 --> 00:08:31.950
yeah there is a
minority of users.

00:08:31.950 --> 00:08:35.370
But they are going to generate
a lot of videos for me

00:08:35.370 --> 00:08:38.070
that have a lot
of ads for me that

00:08:38.070 --> 00:08:40.100
have high click-through rates.

00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:41.690
So that's something
to think about.

00:08:41.690 --> 00:08:44.230
And then again, with
the YouTube API's, we

00:08:44.230 --> 00:08:45.760
allow you to do
some extra things,

00:08:45.760 --> 00:08:49.897
like in the description, you can
set a link to your store links.

