You need to pipe them
through something

00:11:33.050 --> 00:11:34.655
that will encode them for you.

00:11:34.655 --> 00:11:37.290
You can use web m
or maybe FFmpeg,

00:11:37.290 --> 00:11:38.740
if that's better for you.

00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:42.430
In this case, encoding to VP8
for the video, and then Vorbis

00:11:42.430 --> 00:11:43.470
for the audio.

00:11:43.470 --> 00:11:45.960
And you put in a
container, like web m.

00:11:45.960 --> 00:11:47.690
And then bam, you
have your video file.

00:11:47.690 --> 00:11:50.740
Now is when our API step in.

00:11:50.740 --> 00:11:53.910
And you can use-- we have tons
of client libraries in all

00:11:53.910 --> 00:11:55.020
the major languages.

00:11:55.020 --> 00:11:56.728
And we've written
samples in all of them.

00:11:56.728 --> 00:12:01.660
So it's pretty easy for you
just go, pick up an API sample,

00:12:01.660 --> 00:12:03.530
make some minor
modifications, and you're

00:12:03.530 --> 00:12:05.050
pretty much ready go.

00:12:05.050 --> 00:12:07.134
So that's pretty much it.

00:12:07.134 --> 00:12:08.550
It's a RESTful
API, but, again, we

00:12:08.550 --> 00:12:11.910
have client libraries to
handle a lot of this for you.

00:12:11.910 --> 00:12:13.830
Now, let's say,
that's a lot of work.

00:12:13.830 --> 00:12:16.310
And you're like, I don't
want to make the videos.

00:12:16.310 --> 00:12:19.110
There's actually companies out
there that do this for you.

00:12:19.110 --> 00:12:21.070
So Everyplay's a good example.

00:12:21.070 --> 00:12:22.520
They actually
provide an SDK where

00:12:22.520 --> 00:12:23.790
they do everything for you.

00:12:23.790 --> 00:12:25.120
So they make the video.

00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:27.700
And then they allow the
user to upload to YouTube.

00:12:27.700 --> 00:12:30.999
And they've done this
for a lot of games.

00:12:30.999 --> 00:12:32.540
I'm sure you guys
recognize this one.

00:12:32.540 --> 00:12:34.047
This is one.

00:12:34.047 --> 00:12:36.005
And then there's another
company called kamcord

00:12:36.005 --> 00:12:37.575
that does the same thing.

00:12:37.575 --> 00:12:39.260
They have a bunch
of games as well.

00:12:39.260 --> 00:12:41.021
Trial Xtreme 3 is one.

00:12:41.021 --> 00:12:43.270
So if you do a really cool
trick, you can share it up.

00:12:43.270 --> 00:12:47.370
And again, these are just SDKs
that you add to your game.

00:12:47.370 --> 00:12:49.810
And they take care
of all this for you.

00:12:49.810 --> 00:12:51.490
So at least for
Replay, hopefully, that

00:12:51.490 --> 00:12:54.370
gives you a little bit of an
idea of some of the things

00:12:54.370 --> 00:12:55.840
you can do.

00:12:55.840 --> 00:12:58.890
So live is a little
bit different.

00:12:58.890 --> 00:13:00.500
We have a couple
people that do it.

00:13:00.500 --> 00:13:01.860
So Elgato is a big one.

00:13:01.860 --> 00:13:04.360
They're actually
separate hardware.

00:13:04.360 --> 00:13:07.880
But they allow you to stream
live from their device

00:13:07.880 --> 00:13:09.130
up to YouTube.

00:13:09.130 --> 00:13:11.172
Now you can do it with a
console, or it's mobile.

00:13:11.172 --> 00:13:13.046
If you want to do
something a little bit more

00:13:13.046 --> 00:13:15.420
like you saw here with Capella,
they have a live studio,

00:13:15.420 --> 00:13:17.420
where you can do all
sorts of crazy stuff

00:13:17.420 --> 00:13:21.800
with the green screen, crop out
people, put text, and then live

00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:24.110
stream right up.

00:13:24.110 --> 00:13:25.320
Wow how did they do that?

00:13:25.320 --> 00:13:28.550
So this one is our-- actually
our live streaming API.

00:13:28.550 --> 00:13:30.230
Pretty straightforward.

00:13:30.230 --> 00:13:32.270
There's three main
parts to it, really,

00:13:32.270 --> 00:13:33.750
probably only two
you'll be using.

00:13:33.750 --> 00:13:36.720
But you create a broadcast
bind a stream to it,

00:13:36.720 --> 00:13:38.060
and you're pretty much set.

00:13:38.060 --> 00:13:40.320
There is a cue point,
but that's for ads,

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:43.280
and not everyone uses that.

00:13:43.280 --> 00:13:47.340
So anyway, that hopefully
gives you some ideas for replay

00:13:47.340 --> 00:13:48.870
